[As I believed that NDv strains are usually fairly constant in their
lethality, I copied this report to various folk, whose replies
follow - Mod.MHJ
[2
From: Peter.Thornber@affa.gov.au
Date: Wed, 9 Dec 1998 15:03:32 +1100

You will be aware that this information about the source of our outbreak
arising from an endemic strain was relayed to OIE in our official reports
from the Australian Chief Veterinary Officer. This was posted on PROMED as
official information and so has already been made available to all subscribers.
.... It would be unfortunate if ... people got the impression that mutated
virus was all over Australia. As per the last report to OIE, more than
27,000 swabs and sera were collected from over 100 farms, wild birds
sampled, comprehensive passive surveillance undertaken and no further
evidence has been detected. Studies (including gene sequencing) are continuing.
---
Peter Thornber
Special Veterinary Assistant
